{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"UltraliteSDK"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"scrolled","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"done","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"title":"scrolled(done:)","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:12UltraliteSDK12ScrollLayoutC12AutoScrollerC8scrolled4doneySb_tF"},"abstract":[{"text":"delegate callback.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/scrolled(done:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"scrolled","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"done","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]}],"kind":"declarations"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/scrolled(done:)"},"references":{"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout":{"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout","type":"topic","title":"ScrollLayout","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","abstract":[{"text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ScrollLayout"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"abstract":[{"text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","title":"UltraliteSDK"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AutoScroller"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This class was written using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ScrollLayout"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the ","type":"text"},{"code":"duration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It can support any language that the font supports."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LiveText"},{"text":" instance instead).","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller/scrolled(done:)":{"abstract":[{"text":"delegate callback.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/scrolled(done:)","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"scrolled"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"done"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"title":"scrolled(done:)","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/scrolled(done:)"}}}